==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypogæic
<hw>Hyp`o*g⟦ae⟧"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hypo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>gai^a</grk>, <grk>gh^</grk>, earth.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or obtained from, the peanut, or
earthnut (<spn>Arachis hypog⟦ae⟧a</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hypog⟦ae⟧ic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>an
acid in the oil of the earthnut, in which it exists as a glyceride, and
from which it is extracted as a white, crystalline
substance.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypogastric</ent>⟦br⟧
